{
  "dashboard": {
    "title": "Credit Model - Calibration & Performance",
    "tags": ["credit", "calibration", "model"],
    "timezone": "browser",
    "schemaVersion": 16,
    "version": 0,
    "refresh": "1m",
    "panels": [
      {
        "id": 1,
        "title": "Model Calibration Status",
        "type": "stat",
        "gridPos": {"h": 6, "w": 8, "x": 0, "y": 0},
        "targets": [
          {
            "expr": "model_is_calibrated",
            "refId": "A",
            "legendFormat": "Is Calibrated"
          }
        ],
        "description": "Indicates whether the model is using probability calibration (1=yes, 0=no)",
        "fieldConfig": {
          "defaults": {
            "mappings": [
              {
                "type": "value",
                "options": {
                  "0": {"text": "Not Calibrated", "color": "yellow"},
                  "1": {"text": "Calibrated", "color": "green"}
                }
              }
            ],
            "thresholds": {
              "mode": "absolute",
              "steps": [
                {"value": 0, "color": "yellow"},
                {"value": 1, "color": "green"}
              ]
            }
          }
        },
        "options": {
          "colorMode": "background",
          "graphMode": "none",
          "textMode": "value_and_name"
        }
      },
      {
        "id": 2,
        "title": "Brier Score",
        "type": "gauge",
        "gridPos": {"h": 6, "w": 8, "x": 8, "y": 0},
        "targets": [
          {
            "expr": "model_calibration_brier_score",
            "refId": "A",
            "legendFormat": "Brier Score"
          }
        ],
        "description": "Mean squared error between predicted probabilities and outcomes. Lower is better. <0.10 is excellent, 0.10-0.15 is good, >0.20 is poor.",
        "fieldConfig": {
          "defaults": {
            "thresholds": {
              "mode": "absolute",
              "steps": [
                {"value": 0, "color": "green"},
                {"value": 0.10, "color": "yellow"},
                {"value": 0.20, "color": "red"}
              ]
            },
            "min": 0,
            "max": 0.30,
            "unit": "short",
            "decimals": 4
          }
        },
        "options": {
          "showThresholdLabels": true,
          "showThresholdMarkers": true
        }
      },
      {
        "id": 3,
        "title": "CV Score Summary",
        "type": "stat",
        "gridPos": {"h": 6, "w": 8, "x": 16, "y": 0},
        "targets": [
          {
            "expr": "model_cv_score_mean",
            "refId": "A",
            "legendFormat": "Mean"
          },
          {
            "expr": "model_cv_score_std",
            "refId": "B",
            "legendFormat": "Std Dev"
          }
        ],
        "description": "Cross-validation scores from model training",
        "fieldConfig": {
          "defaults": {
            "unit": "percentunit",
            "decimals": 3
          },
          "overrides": [
            {
              "matcher": {"id": "byName", "options": "Mean"},
              "properties": [
                {
                  "id": "thresholds",
                  "value": {
                    "mode": "absolute",
                    "steps": [
                      {"value": 0, "color": "red"},
                      {"value": 0.75, "color": "yellow"},
                      {"value": 0.85, "color": "green"}
                    ]
                  }
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "matcher": {"id": "byName", "options": "Std Dev"},
              "properties": [
                {
                  "id": "thresholds",
                  "value": {
                    "mode": "absolute",
                    "steps": [
                      {"value": 0, "color": "green"},
                      {"value": 0.02, "color": "yellow"},
                      {"value": 0.05, "color": "red"}
                    ]
                  }
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        "options": {
          "colorMode": "background",
          "graphMode": "none"
        }
      },
      {
        "id": 4,
        "title": "Brier Score Over Time",
        "type": "graph",
        "gridPos": {"h": 8, "w": 24, "x": 0, "y": 6},
        "targets": [
          {
            "expr": "model_calibration_brier_score",
            "refId": "A",
            "legendFormat": "Brier Score"
          }
        ],
        "yaxes": [
          {"format": "short", "logBase": 1, "min": 0, "max": 0.30},
          {"format": "short", "logBase": 1}
        ],
        "legend": {
          "show": true,
          "alignAsTable": true,
          "avg": true,
          "current": true,
          "max": true,
          "min": true
        },
        "thresholds": [
          {"value": 0.10, "colorMode": "custom", "fillColor": "rgba(255, 255, 0, 0.1)", "line": true},
          {"value": 0.20, "colorMode": "critical", "fillColor": "rgba(255, 0, 0, 0.1)", "line": true}
        ],
        "alert": {
          "conditions": [
            {
              "evaluator": {"params": [0.20], "type": "gt"},
              "operator": {"type": "and"},
              "query": {"params": ["A", "5m", "now"]},
              "reducer": {"params": [], "type": "avg"},
              "type": "query"
            }
          ],
          "executionErrorState": "alerting",
          "frequency": "60s",
          "handler": 1,
          "name": "Poor Calibration Alert",
          "message": "Model calibration has degraded. Brier score > 0.20. Consider recalibrating the model.",
          "noDataState": "no_data",
          "notifications": []
        }
      },
      {
        "id": 5,
        "title": "Feature Drift Detection",
        "type": "graph",
        "gridPos": {"h": 8, "w": 24, "x": 0, "y": 14},
        "targets": [
          {
            "expr": "model_feature_drift",
            "refId": "A",
            "legendFormat": "{{feature}}"
          }
        ],
        "description": "Feature drift scores (0-1). Higher values indicate more drift from training distribution.",
        "yaxes": [
          {"format": "percentunit", "logBase": 1, "min": 0, "max": 1},
          {"format": "short", "logBase": 1}
        ],
        "legend": {
          "show": true,
          "alignAsTable": true,
          "avg": true,
          "current": true,
          "max": true,
          "hideEmpty": true,
          "hideZero": true
        },
        "thresholds": [
          {"value": 0.1, "colorMode": "custom", "fillColor": "rgba(255, 255, 0, 0.1)", "line": true},
          {"value": 0.3, "colorMode": "critical", "fillColor": "rgba(255, 0, 0, 0.1)", "line": true}
        ]
      },
      {
        "id": 6,
        "title": "Model Performance Summary",
        "type": "table",
        "gridPos": {"h": 8, "w": 12, "x": 0, "y": 22},
        "targets": [
          {
            "expr": "model_accuracy",
            "refId": "A",
            "format": "table",
            "instant": true
          },
          {
            "expr": "model_cv_score_mean",
            "refId": "B",
            "format": "table",
            "instant": true
          },
          {
            "expr": "model_cv_score_std",
            "refId": "C",
            "format": "table",
            "instant": true
          },
          {
            "expr": "model_calibration_brier_score",
            "refId": "D",
            "format": "table",
            "instant": true
          },
          {
            "expr": "model_is_calibrated",
            "refId": "E",
            "format": "table",
            "instant": true
          }
        ],
        "transformations": [
          {
            "id": "merge",
            "options": {}
          },
          {
            "id": "organize",
            "options": {
              "renameByName": {
                "Value #A": "Accuracy",
                "Value #B": "CV Mean",
                "Value #C": "CV Std",
                "Value #D": "Brier Score",
                "Value #E": "Is Calibrated"
              }
            }
          }
        ],
        "options": {
          "showHeader": true
        },
        "fieldConfig": {
          "overrides": [
            {
              "matcher": {"id": "byName", "options": "Accuracy"},
              "properties": [
                {"id": "unit", "value": "percentunit"},
                {"id": "decimals", "value": 3},
                {"id": "custom.displayMode", "value": "color-background"},
                {
                  "id": "thresholds",
                  "value": {
                    "mode": "absolute",
                    "steps": [
                      {"value": 0, "color": "red"},
                      {"value": 0.75, "color": "yellow"},
                      {"value": 0.85, "color": "green"}
                    ]
                  }
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "matcher": {"id": "byName", "options": "Brier Score"},
              "properties": [
                {"id": "decimals", "value": 4},
                {"id": "custom.displayMode", "value": "color-background"},
                {
                  "id": "thresholds",
                  "value": {
                    "mode": "absolute",
                    "steps": [
                      {"value": 0, "color": "green"},
                      {"value": 0.10, "color": "yellow"},
                      {"value": 0.20, "color": "red"}
                    ]
                  }
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "id": 7,
        "title": "Calibration Recommendations",
        "type": "text",
        "gridPos": {"h": 8, "w": 12, "x": 12, "y": 22},
        "options": {
          "mode": "markdown",
          "content": "## Calibration Guidelines\n\n### Brier Score Interpretation:\n- **< 0.10**: Excellent calibration\n- **0.10 - 0.15**: Good calibration\n- **0.15 - 0.20**: Acceptable calibration\n- **> 0.20**: Poor calibration - consider recalibrating\n\n### When to Recalibrate:\n1. Brier score > 0.20\n2. Significant feature drift detected\n3. Data distribution changes\n4. Every 3-6 months as precaution\n\n### Actions:\n```bash\n# Recalibrate model\npython -m src.main calibrate \\\n  --model-path models/credit_model.pkl \\\n  --data-path data/recent_data.csv\n\n# Evaluate calibration\npython -m src.main cv \\\n  --data-path data/validation_data.csv\n```\n\n### Monitoring:\n- Set up alerts for Brier score > 0.20\n- Monitor feature drift regularly\n- Track calibration status over time"
        }
      }
    ]
  }
}
